# Hotel Bookings: Analysis


### Sets up environment
```{r}
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
```

### Creates Dataframe
```{r}
hotel_bookings <- read.csv("/cloud/project/Course 7/Week 4/hotel_bookings.csv")
```

### Previews sample of dataset
```{r}
head(hotel_bookings)
colnames(hotel_bookings)
```

### Creates different plots for each type of hotel to compare market segments, angles text on x axis to make wording easier to read
```{r}
ggplot(data = hotel_bookings) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = market_segment)) +
  facet_wrap(~hotel) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45))
```

### Filters through the data to pull Online TA segments for City Hotels
```{r}
Online_TA_City_Hotels <- hotel_bookings %>% 
  filter(hotel == 'City Hotel') %>% 
  filter(market_segment == 'Online TA')
```

### Filters through the data to pull Online TA segments for Resort Hotels
```{r}
Online_TA_Resort_Hotels <- hotel_bookings %>% 
  filter(hotel == 'Resort Hotel') %>% 
  filter(market_segment == 'Online TA')
```

### Creates min and max dates to create captions 
```{r}
mindate <- min(hotel_bookings$arrival_date_year)
maxdate <- max(hotel_bookings$arrival_date_year)
```

### Creates labels and captions to make data easier to understand
```{r}
ggplot(data = hotel_bookings) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = market_segment)) +
  facet_wrap(~hotel) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45)) +
  labs(title = "Market Segments Between City Hotels 
       and Resort Hotels", 
       caption = paste0("Data from: ", mindate, " to ", maxdate))

```




